          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8151-9f14-cd21dc7c072b",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Time-traveling via a pocket device to solve puzzles between a vibrant 70s and a desolate future. A sleek, minimalist gem."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81d9-8585-f3a1b907b9df",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The Kickstarter darling that revived the genre. Part 1 was pure "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "magic"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "underline": true,
              "color": "purple"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": ", even if Part 2 leaned a bit too hard into frustrating backtracking."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81e3-b4a7-d63871757fd8",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Urban fantasy meets BioWare-style party mechanics in a point-and-click adventure. The best thing Wadjet Eye has ever produced."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81fd-b9fe-c5a36c3206ce",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The greatest Indiana Jones movie never made. Three different paths to play through? LucasArts was just flexing at this point."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8134-877c-eafe0dac795f",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "A melancholic, atmospheric journey filled with clockwork automatons and Soviet-era decay. Kate Walker's transformation is incredibly compelling."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8182-807c-cf4e14c7a9be",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The true successor to Obra Dinn. Filling out those mad libs of "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "murder"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "red"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " using pure deductive reasoning makes you feel like an absolute genius."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8191-a859-e68730b4ed58",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The monkey wrench puzzle alone makes this infamous, but the ending remains one of the boldest, most debated conclusions in gaming history."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81f0-bd3e-c9ebb1f54b10",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "An "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "epic"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": ", sprawling narrative bridging "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "magic"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "underline": true,
              "color": "purple"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " and science. April Ryan is a "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "legendary"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " protagonist, and Arcadia feels like a living, breathing world."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-818d-b9b3-e2a06d0c045c",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Isometric post-apocalyptic Africa with some of the most striking, "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "bizarre"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "italic": true,
              "color": "gray"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " environmental art you'll ever see."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8112-94d4-cbdf77b77255",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Southern Gothic "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "mystery"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "italic": true,
              "color": "gray"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " dripping with atmosphere. Tim Curry's "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "legendary"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": ", wildly inconsistent New Orleans accent is the cherry on top."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8174-b237-dfae3c74c9de",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "A "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "masterclass"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " in rain-slicked, pixel-art "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "cyberpunk"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "underline": true,
              "color": "purple"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " noir. The twist regarding the two protagonists still hits hard."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-814a-b8c5-ed63969076a1",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Ron Gilbert returning to his baby. The art style grew on everyone, and the ending is a "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "beautiful"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": ", meta reflection on why we play these games."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-8102-894d-de8919f62539",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Disco Elysium meets D&D politics. Playing a "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "cynical"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "italic": true,
              "color": "gray"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " cleric navigating a fantasy election is exactly the kind of chaotic roleplay we need."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-81f7-8290-d946e9e36c9c",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Pure teenage nostalgia distilled into a playable mixtape. I can already hear the licensed indie soundtrack echoing in my head."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-81bd-9367-dfe5448b232b",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Hella emotional. Come for the time-traveling hipster photography, stay for the devastating trolley problems and the indie-folk soundtrack."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-8124-9d1c-d7766b7158f3",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The ultimate 'walkie-talkie simulator'. A "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "beautiful"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": ", lonely hike through the Wyoming wilderness that hits you with a surprisingly grounded emotional gut-punch."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-81ed-8a2e-d8cb21681cb9",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "A wordless "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "masterpiece"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " of rusty robot charm and deviously difficult puzzles. Amanita Design at its absolute peak."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-8102-96b1-f42150fe34f5",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Voxel-based replicant hunting! It captured the gritty, neon-drenched mood of the film perfectly, even if the real-time elements induced pure panic."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-81ce-a421-c034563dc232",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "PRESS X TO JASON! A messy, ambitious interactive drama that walked so Detroit: Become Human could run. The origami killer "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "mystery"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "italic": true,
              "color": "gray"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " still grips."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-8140-bffd-e68e8038ae2a",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The walking-and-talking system is unparalleled. Nothing like a casual teen beach party turning into a "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "terrifying"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "red"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": ", time-looping radio frequency "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "nightmare"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "red"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-81d0-86d4-cc4f2fdb5e8e",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "The game that sparked a thousand 'what is a game' debates. A masterful exercise in environmental storytelling and 90s riot grrrl nostalgia."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-8171-9169-d3afcde6a1c0",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "David Cage's slickest, most branching flowchart of a game. Connor and Hank's buddy-cop dynamic carries the whole android revolution on its shoulders."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a4d3e6d-60db-8114-a6f0-fb8c128f2084",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Elliot Page and Willem Dafoe trapped in a wild, chronologically fractured fever dream of CIA espionage and poltergeist action."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81db-8809-cbb17254ec94",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "A surreal, Southern Gothic "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "cyberpunk"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "underline": true,
              "color": "purple"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " trip through a decaying Louisiana. The writing is so thick and atmospheric you can practically smell the swamp."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81b4-b204-ddddabdf57a2",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Spielberg's "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "sci-fi"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "underline": true,
              "color": "purple"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "epic"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " translated into a punishingly difficult adventure game. The atmosphere is top-notch, but that turtle bone puzzle is pure evil."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-8189-9ad5-c2e98d62d76f",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "A delightful, meta-heavy nostalgia trip to the golden age of SCUMM. The humor is sharp, the pixels are chunky, and the ending is beautifully divisive."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81b2-af19-eb5b508b2c1b",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "I am a superstar cop. A staggering achievement in writing, where your own fragmented psyche is both your greatest asset and worst enemy."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-818a-b818-e12d9b339853",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "More of a play than a game. "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Beautiful"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "page_id": "3a3d3e6d-60db-81eb-b5a0-c6c97dfecfc2",
    "properties": {
      "Journal/Notes": {
        "rich_text": [
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "Manny Calavera is iconic. A "
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": "brilliant"
            },
            "annotations": {
              "bold": true,
              "color": "orange"
            }
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "content": " fusion of Aztec mythology and film noir. The tank controls are painful, but the writing is unparalleled."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
]